entries.title: 'Polo Polo,' popular Mexican comedian, dead at 78
entries.description: Mexican comedian Leopoldo Roberto Garcia Pelaez Benitez, who performed as "Polo Polo," died on Monday, his family announced.

entries.title: Iconic London hotel reveals lavish transformation
entries.description: Cocktails are served.

entries.title: Russia believed to have directed White supremacists to carry out bombings in Spain, US says
entries.description: US officials believe that Russian intelligence officers directed a Russian White supremacist group to carry out a letter-bombing campaign that rocked Madrid late last year, targeting the prime minister, the American and Ukrainian Embassies as well as the Spanish defense ministry, according to current and former US officials.

entries.title: Multiple people injured in Des Moines shooting, police say
entries.description: Police in Des Moines, Iowa, are on the scene of a shooting incident, with multiple injuries, according to a Twitter post from the department.

entries.title: Oath Keepers members found guilty of seditious conspiracy
entries.description: Three members of the Oath Keepers and a fourth person associated with the far-right militia group were convicted of seditious conspiracy by a Washington, DC, jury on Monday for their role in the January 6, 2021, insurrection.

entries.title: Argentina and Brazil are discussing a common currency. Don't hold your breath
entries.description: The two biggest economies in South America are starting talks to create a common currency. Analysts are skeptical.

entries.title: Former high-level FBI official charged in alleged schemes to help sanctioned Russian oligarch and conceal payments from ex-Albanian intel official
entries.description: The former head of counterintelligence for the FBI's New York field office was charged in two separate indictments Monday for allegedly working with a sanctioned Russian oligarch after he retired and concealing hundreds of thousands of dollars he received from a former employee of an Albanian intelligence agency while he was a top official at the bureau.

entries.title: The Washington Post is not for sale, owner Jeff Bezos and the newspaper say
entries.description: The Washington Post is not for sale, spokespeople for the newspaper and its owner Jeff Bezos told CNN on Monday.

entries.title: '420 price was not a joke.' Elon Musk testifies again in trial over controversial tweet
entries.description: Tesla CEO Elon Musk took the witness stand for a second day on Monday and attempted to explain the thought process behind his controversial "funding secured" tweet from 2018, pushing back at the idea that it was partly a joke.

entries.title: Webb telescope spies frozen molecules inside a wispy space cloud
entries.description: The James Webb Space Telescope peered inside a wispy molecular cloud located 630 light-years away and spied ices made of different elements.

entries.title: Seized artifacts worth $20 million are shown off on return to Italy
entries.description: Italy celebrated the return of 60 ancient artifacts worth more than $20 million from the United States with a display in Rome's Spadolini Hall on Monday.

entries.title: Don't say 'mummy': Why museums are rebranding ancient Egyptian remains
entries.description: They are among the most popular exhibits in museums worldwide, with a name so resonant, blockbuster films have been built on it.

entries.title: Man who rested feet on desk in Pelosi's office on Jan. 6 found guilty on 8 counts
entries.description: An Arkansas man who was infamously photographed putting his feet on a desk inside then-House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's office during the January 6, 2021, insurrection was found guilty on eight counts by a Washington, DC, jury Monday.

entries.title: Tim Allen denies flashing Pamela Anderson on 'Home Improvement' set
entries.description: In her new memoir, Pamela Anderson is detailing a disturbing incident she says happened on the set of "Home Improvement" with her former costar Tim Allen.

entries.title: Many women underestimate breast density as a risk factor for breast cancer, study shows
entries.description: Dense breast tissue has been associated with up to a four times higher risk of breast cancer. However, a new study suggests few women view breast density as a significant risk factor.

entries.title: Ford plans 3,200 job cuts in Europe as it moves some work to the US
entries.description: Ford plans to cut 3,200 jobs across Europe and move some product development work to the United States, Germany's IG Metall union said on Monday, vowing action that would disrupt the carmaker across the continent if the cuts go ahead.

entries.title: Kylie Jenner reveals son's name and how to pronounce it
entries.description: Kylie Jenner finally revealed her son's name over the weekend, just before his first birthday.

entries.title: George Santos' pattern of lies is putting scrutiny on this GOP lawmaker
entries.description: Revelations about New York Rep. George Santos' pattern of lies and deception are putting increased scrutiny on  New York Rep. Elise Stefanik, the fourth-ranking House Republican and a vocal supporter of Santos during his 2022 campaign. CNN's chief investigative correspondent Pam Brown has more.

entries.title: Iran's regime is trying to execute its way out of trouble
entries.description: The cries of the women outside a Tehran courthouse swell to a collective wail. The gathering is reminiscent of a vigil, but it is one of the vestiges of a nationwide uprising that has all but died down after the Iranian judiciary's breathless handing down of death sentences in recent weeks.

entries.title: Microsoft confirms it's investing billions in ChatGPT creator OpenAI
entries.description: Microsoft on Monday confirmed it is making a "multibillion dollar" investment in OpenAI,  the company behind the viral new chatbot tool called ChatGPT.

entries.title: US and Israel launch largest military exercise ever despite concerns over Netanyahu's government
entries.description: The US and Israel launched their largest joint military exercise ever on Monday, sending a clear signal to Iran and underscoring the strength of their alliance despite concerns over the composition of the new Israeli government which includes ultra-nationalist and ultra-religious parties.

entries.title: Razzies announce nominations led by 'Blonde'
entries.description: Nominations for the 43rd Annual Razzie Awards were announced Monday and it was a good (or bad) day for "Blonde," Disney's "Pinocchio" and "Morbius."

entries.title: Dallas Cowboys: 'America's Team' returns to the drawing board after suffering another disappointing playoff defeat
entries.description: It's déjà vu for the Dallas Cowboys.

entries.title: Salesforce under siege from top activist hedge fund
entries.description: Software giant Salesforce, one of the 30 stocks in the venerable Dow Jones Industrial Average, had a miserable 2022. Now the company is under attack from a big hedge fund that wants to shake things up at the company that owns Slack.

entries.title: With 50 points from 19 games, Arsenal is in pole position to win a surprise Premier League title
entries.description: "Extraordinary" is how manager Mikel Arteta summed up Arsenal's season so far -- and few would disagree.

entries.title: This dead fish head pie is worth waiting for
entries.description: On a hot summer day in the Cornish seaside village of Mousehole. In the kitchen of The Old Coastguard hotel, chef Jamie Porter is bent low over a bench, unfolding a marvelous fish fantasy that's all heads, no tails.

entries.title: Meteorologist attacked by teens on subway
entries.description: Fox meteorologist Adam Klotz says he was attacked over the weekend by a group of teens on a New York City subway. CNN's Brynn Gingras has the report.

entries.title: Man recounts moment he pointed gun at Monterey Park suspect
entries.description: Brandon Tsay, the man who encountered and disarmed the suspect of the Alhambra dance hall shooting that killed 10 people and injured 10 others, describes the moment he came face to face with the gunman.

entries.title: Jon Rahm continues blistering form with second-straight PGA Tour title at The American Express
entries.description: Sunday was the start of Lunar New Year, the Year of the Rabbit. In the golfing calendar, it marked a continuation of the year of Jon Rahm.

entries.title: House Democratic whip's daughter arrested in Boston at protest
entries.description: House Democratic Whip Katherine Clark's daughter was arrested and charged with assault after an encounter with police during a protest in Boston on Saturday, according to a press release from the Boston Police Department.

entries.title: Biden sends message to Aubrey Plaza as she hosts 'Saturday Night Live'
entries.description: Actress Aubrey Plaza talked about her time as an NBC Page, and treated viewers to a tour of the "Saturday Night Live" studio.

entries.title: Blue Ivy takes stage with mom Beyoncé in Dubai
entries.description: Talent runs deep in the Carter family.

entries.title: Greatest trade ever? Citadel's $16 billion haul smashes hedge fund records
entries.description: Citadel is now the most successful hedge fund ever after it made $16 billion last year — the biggest annual windfall on record.

entries.title: Everything you need to know about Kylie Jenner's lion's head outfit
entries.description: Nothing says fierce like using an apex predator as a brooch. On Monday, Kylie Jenner stole the show at Schiaparelli's couture runway in Paris when she arrived in a black velvet strapless gown adorned with the life-size head of a lion — a pre-release from the label's Spring-Summer 2023 couture collection that debuted moments later.

entries.title: Spotify to cut 6% of its workforce
entries.description: Spotify said Monday that it will cut 6% of its global workforce to reduce costs, joining tech companies including Amazon and Microsoft in slashing headcount as the global economy slows.

entries.title: Natural Light is tapping into nostalgia with its new can design
entries.description: Natural Light's new cans will soon look a lot like their old ones.

entries.title: ​​Sebastian Korda: The rising US tennis star who is the 'worst athlete in the family'
entries.description: Sebastian Korda may have knocked out some of the world's best players and is preparing for his first Australian Open quarterfinal, but the 22-year-old still says he's the "worst athlete" in his family.

entries.title: These volunteers are bringing aid to front lines in Ukraine
entries.description: CNN's Ben Wedeman speaks with volunteers who are helping to help evacuate communities on the front lines in Ukraine.

entries.title: Why is Britain's health service, a much-loved national treasure, falling apart?
entries.description: Most winters, headlines warn that Britain's National Health Service (NHS) is at "breaking point." The alarms sound over and over and over again. But the current crisis has set warning bells ringing louder than before.

entries.title: Opinion: Hypocrisy to the max on debt ceiling
entries.description: So here we go again. Another dramatic, high-stakes debt ceiling debate is about to unfold. Not lost on the American people during these hypertension-inducing episodes is the stunning political hypocrisy revealed through debt ceiling kerfuffles.

entries.title: Australian Open: Novak Djokovic cruises past Alex de Minaur in straight sets to reach quarterfinals
entries.description: Novak Djokovic was in imperious form once again as he cruised past Alex de Minaur in straight sets to reach the Australian Open quarterfinals.

entries.title: Asia's richest man Gautam Adani is addicted to ChatGPT
entries.description: Asia's richest man Gautam Adani says he is addicted to ChatGPT, the powerful new AI tool that interacts with users in an eerily convincing and conversational way.

entries.title: Croatia's secret beaches and little Venices
entries.description: Head to Croatia's northern Adriatic coast to discover some of the country's most captivating regions. While Dubrovnik and other parts of southern Dalmatia get the lion's share of attention, the Istrian peninsula and the neighboring islands and coastal ports of the Kvarner Gulf reveal other sides of Croatia's rich culture and history.

entries.title: Trilobites armed with tridents could be the earliest known example of sexual combat
entries.description: From a deer's elaborate branching antlers to the fiddler crab's oversize claw, the animal kingdom is full of flashy features used in combat to help secure a mate.

entries.title: Sal Bando, former MLB All-Star and World Series champion, dies at 78
entries.description: Sal Bando, a former four-time Major League Baseball (MLB) All-Star and three-time World Series champion, has died at the age of 78, the league announced on Saturday.

entries.title: 'Maybe they knew something we didn't': New Netflix series goes behind the scenes on golf's most controversial year
entries.description: Heated arguments, high stakes, and maximum tension; Netflix's "Drive to Survive" docuseries delves behind the curtain into the turbulent careers of Formula One drivers.

entries.title: India bans BBC documentary on PM Modi's role in Gujarat riots
entries.description: India has banned a BBC documentary critical of Prime Minister Narendra Modi's alleged role in deadly riots more than 20 years ago from being shown in the country, in a move critics decried as an assault on press freedom.

entries.title: Germany won't stop Poland sending Leopard combat tanks to Ukraine if asked, official says
What we know about the suspect
entries.description: The 72-year-old man suspected of killing 10 people and wounding 10 others in a shooting at a dance studio in Monterey Park, California, Saturday had previously frequented the establishment, sources told CNN.

entries.title: What we know: Investigators search for motive of suspected gunman Huu Can Tran
entries.description: Investigators in Monterey Park, California, are still searching for the motive of a gunman who killed 10 people and injured 10 others during a shooting inside a ballroom dance studio Saturday night, devastating the majority-Asian community on the eve of its Lunar New Year celebration.

entries.title: There have been more US mass shootings than days in 2023
The man shot himself inside a van after a standoff with police about 30 miles from the mass shooting in which 10 people were killed
72-year-old man suspected in California massacre is dead

Former tennis star Jelena Dokic slams trolls over offensive posts about her body
entries.description: Former Australian tennis star Jelena Dokic has hit back at online trolls she says have bombarded her with negative comments about her body at the Australian Open.

entries.title: FBI search deepens political implications of Biden document discoveries
What we know: Sheriff identifies suspect as Huu Can Tran
Why K-pop rules fashion week
entries.description: Outside Prada's menswear show in Milan earlier this month, the street was packed with screaming fans, most of whom seemed to have turned out for Korean pop group Enhypen, who attended the event. Devotees at times broke into song, intoning the boy band's hits.

entries.title: Nearly 220 million people in Pakistan without power after countrywide outage
entries.description: A nationwide power outage in Pakistan left nearly 220 million people without electricity on Monday, threatening to cause havoc in the South Asian nation already grappling with fuel shortages in the winter months.

entries.title: How to celebrate Lunar New Year like an Emperor
entries.description: It's Lunar New Year. Wearing their finest festive clothes, an 18th century family sits down to feast on a lavish banquet in a room adorned with auspicious signage.

entries.title: There have been more US mass shootings than days in 2023
A group of friends attended a vigil in Beijing. Then one by one, they disappeared
The man, 72, was found dead inside a cargo van after a standoff with police about 30 miles from the shooting in which 10 people were killed
California mass shooting suspect dies from self-inflicted gunshot wound
Video: Sheriff explains how they found the shooting suspect
entries.description: Los Angeles County Sheriff Robert G. Luna describes the investigation that led police to finding the man suspected of killing at least 10 people in a mass shooting in Monterey Park, California, dead of a self-inflicted gunshot.

entries.title: Pelosi shares what she thought about McCarthy's speaker vote
entries.description: Former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi (D-CA) gives CNN's Chris Wallace her reaction to the contentious voting process to make Rep. Kevin McCarthy the new House speaker.

entries.title: Idina Menzel shares the change to 'Let It Go' that she questions
entries.description: Idina Menzel tells CNN's Chris Wallace about the change she made to "Let It Go" from Disney's "Frozen" when she was recording the iconic song.

entries.title: 50 years after Roe, pregnant women are posting their last wishes on TikTok
entries.description: Some pregnant women in America are posting "living wills" on TikTok due to restrictive abortion laws in their states. Ashley Martinez lives in Texas, has four sons and is pregnant with a much-wanted daughter. But she's worried that her life wouldn't be prioritized if she experienced birth complications.

entries.title: 'Senseless attack': Biden offers condolences to victims
entries.description: President Joe Biden offered his condolences to the victims of a mass shooting in California that left 10 dead, while acknowledging the impact on the Asian American and Pacific Islander community in a statement on Sunday.
